{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775861374051,"sessionID":"ses_2866f5bd6ffemB1SA4HazeJvKc","part":{"id":"prt_d79961c2f001LCqiWMs8bDURa2","messageID":"msg_d7995d318001tlmMklWZwwdRQt","sessionID":"ses_2866f5bd6ffemB1SA4HazeJvKc","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_tool-a8806c2485164d99993bbb92fadbb4a1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"cat > /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-017/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md << 'EOF'\n# AR-017 Implementation Summary: PicoD JWT 中间件\n\n## Overview\nSuccessfully implemented complete JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD module, providing secure session authentication for AgentCube platform API endpoints.\n\n## Implementation Status: ✅ COMPLETE\n\n## Components Implemented\n\n### 1. Core Authentication (`pkg/picod/auth.go`)\n- **AuthManager struct**: RSA public key with thread-safe mutex\n- **NewAuthManager()**: Constructor that loads public key from `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable\n- **ValidateToken()**: Token validation with RS256 algorithm, 1-minute clock skew tolerance\n- **AuthClaims struct**: Extends `jwt.RegisteredClaims` for standard JWT claims\n\n### 2. Middleware Layer (`pkg/picod/middleware.go`)\n- **AuthMiddleware()**: Gin middleware function that:\n  - Extracts and validates Authorization header\n  - Enforces \"Bearer <token>\" format\n  - Validates JWT tokens using AuthManager\n  - Stores claims in Gin context\n  - Wraps request body with 32MB size limit\n  - Logs validation failures\n\n### 3. Error Handling (`pkg/picod/errors.go`)\nDefined 6 authentication error constants:\n- `ErrMissingAuthHeader` → 401 Unauthorized\n- `ErrInvalidAuthFormat` → 401 Unauthorized\n- `ErrInvalidToken` → 401 Unauthorized\n- `ErrInvalidSignature` → 401 Unauthorized\n- `ErrTokenExpired` → 401 Unauthorized\n- `ErrInvalidPublicKey` → 500 Internal Server Error\n\n### 4. Constants (`pkg/picod/constants.go`)\n- Environment variable: `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY`\n- HTTP headers: `Authorization`\n- Error messages for all authentication error scenarios\n- Max body size: 32MB (32 << 20)\n\n### 5. Server Integration (`pkg/picod/server.go`)\n- Added `authManager` field to Server struct\n- AuthManager initialization in `NewServer()`\n- Route protection in `registerRoutes()`:\n  - `/api/*` routes require authentication\n  - `/health` endpoint remains public\n\n### 6. Comprehensive Test Coverage\n\n#### Unit Tests (`pkg/picod/auth_test.go`)\n- ✅ AuthManager initialization (success and failure cases)\n- ✅ Public key validation (PEM format, RSA type, parsing errors)\n- ✅ Token validation (valid, invalid signature, expired, malformed)\n- ✅ Clock skew tolerance (1-minute leeway)\n\n#### Middleware Tests (`pkg/picod/middleware_test.go`)\n- ✅ Missing Authorization header\n- ✅ Invalid Authorization formats (Basic, Token, no prefix)\n- ✅ Valid token authentication\n- ✅ Invalid token formats\n- ✅ Expired token handling\n- ✅ Wrong signature detection\n- ✅ Wrong signing algorithm rejection (HS256)\n- ✅ Claims storage in context\n- ✅ Body size limit wrapping\n- ✅ Clock skew tolerance\n- ✅ Request abortion on errors\n\n#### Integration Tests (`pkg/picod/server_test.go`)\n- ✅ AuthManager initialization in Server\n- ✅ Protected route authentication\n- ✅ Public health endpoint access\n- ✅ Server startup with/without public key\n\n## Security Features\n\n1. **RSA Public Key Verification**: Strict validation at startup\n2. **Signature Algorithm Enforcement**: Only RS256 accepted\n3. **Clock Skew Tolerance**: 1-minute leeway for clock drift\n4. **Request Size Limiting**: 32MB maximum body size\n5. **Concurrent Safety**: Read-write mutex protects public key access\n6. **Error Logging**: Warning-level logs for validation failures\n\n## Test Results\n```\n✅ All tests passing\n- TestAuthMiddleware_ErrorCases: PASS\n- TestAuthMiddleware_ValidToken: PASS\n- TestAuthMiddleware_BodySizeWrapped: PASS\n- TestAuthMiddleware_ClockSkewTolerance: PASS\n- TestAuthMiddleware_RequestAbortedOnError: PASS\n- TestNewAuthManager: PASS\n- TestValidateToken: PASS\n- TestNewServer: PASS\n- TestHealthCheckHandler: PASS\n```\n\n## Code Quality\n- ✅ Zero compilation errors\n- ✅ Zero test failures\n- ✅ Follows Go best practices\n- ✅ Proper error handling throughout\n- ✅ Thread-safe implementation\n- ✅ Comprehensive documentation\n\n## API Contracts Matched\n\nAll requirements from delta-spec.md have been implemented:\n\n1. ✅ AuthManager structure and methods\n2. ✅ AuthMiddleware Gin middleware\n3. ✅ Authorization header extraction and validation\n4. ✅ Token verification integration\n5. ✅ Error type definitions\n6. ✅ HTTP status code mappings\n7. ✅ Environment variable constants\n8. ✅ HTTP header constants\n9. ✅ Error message constants\n10. ✅ Request size limit constants\n11. ✅ Server structure extension\n12. ✅ AuthManager initialization\n13. ✅ Route protection\n14. ✅ Error response format\n15. ✅ Logging requirements\n16. ✅ Security considerations\n17. ✅ Concurrent safety\n18. ✅ Test coverage requirements\n\n## Files Modified/Created\n\n### Created:\n- `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go` (344 lines) - Comprehensive middleware tests\n\n### Already Existed (Verified Complete):\n- `pkg/picod/auth.go` - Core authentication logic\n- `pkg/picod/auth_test.go` - Auth unit tests\n- `pkg/picod/middleware.go` - Gin middleware\n- `pkg/picod/errors.go` - Error definitions\n- `pkg/picod/constants.go` - Constants\n- `pkg/picod/server.go` - Server integration\n- `pkg/picod/server_test.go` - Server integration tests\n\n## Usage Example\n\n```bash\n# Set public key environment variable\nexport PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY=\"$(cat public_key.pem)\"\n\n# Start PicoD server\n./picod\n\n# Access protected endpoint with JWT\ncurl -H \"Authorization: Bearer <jwt_token>\" http://localhost:8080/api/execute\n\n# Health check (public, no auth required)\ncurl http://localhost:8080/health\n```\n\n## Conclusion\n\nThe PicoD JWT middleware implementation is **COMPLETE** and **PRODUCTION-READY**. All requirements from AR-017 have been fully implemented with comprehensive test coverage, proper error handling, and security best practices.\nEOF\ncat /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-017/IMPLEMENTATION_SUMMARY.md","description":"Create implementation summary for AR-017"},"output":"# AR-017 Implementation Summary: PicoD JWT 中间件\n\n## Overview\nSuccessfully implemented complete JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD module, providing secure session authentication for AgentCube platform API endpoints.\n\n## Implementation Status: ✅ COMPLETE\n\n## Components Implemented\n\n### 1. Core Authentication (`pkg/picod/auth.go`)\n- **AuthManager struct**: RSA public key with thread-safe mutex\n- **NewAuthManager()**: Constructor that loads public key from `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY` environment variable\n- **ValidateToken()**: Token validation with RS256 algorithm, 1-minute clock skew tolerance\n- **AuthClaims struct**: Extends `jwt.RegisteredClaims` for standard JWT claims\n\n### 2. Middleware Layer (`pkg/picod/middleware.go`)\n- **AuthMiddleware()**: Gin middleware function that:\n  - Extracts and validates Authorization header\n  - Enforces \"Bearer <token>\" format\n  - Validates JWT tokens using AuthManager\n  - Stores claims in Gin context\n  - Wraps request body with 32MB size limit\n  - Logs validation failures\n\n### 3. Error Handling (`pkg/picod/errors.go`)\nDefined 6 authentication error constants:\n- `ErrMissingAuthHeader` → 401 Unauthorized\n- `ErrInvalidAuthFormat` → 401 Unauthorized\n- `ErrInvalidToken` → 401 Unauthorized\n- `ErrInvalidSignature` → 401 Unauthorized\n- `ErrTokenExpired` → 401 Unauthorized\n- `ErrInvalidPublicKey` → 500 Internal Server Error\n\n### 4. Constants (`pkg/picod/constants.go`)\n- Environment variable: `PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY`\n- HTTP headers: `Authorization`\n- Error messages for all authentication error scenarios\n- Max body size: 32MB 