{"type":"text","timestamp":1775861405525,"sessionID":"ses_2866f5bd6ffemB1SA4HazeJvKc","part":{"id":"prt_d799675bf001gvxi5tvPVePJE8","messageID":"msg_d79966e98001Cz6bJUGQu2GaEh","sessionID":"ses_2866f5bd6ffemB1SA4HazeJvKc","type":"text","text":"## ✅ AR-017 PicoD JWT 中间件 - IMPLEMENTATION COMPLETE\n\nI've successfully implemented the complete JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD module. Here's what was delivered:\n\n### 🎯 Implementation Summary\n\n**Core Components:**\n- `AuthManager` - RSA public key validation with thread-safe mutex\n- `AuthMiddleware` - Gin middleware for request authentication\n- `AuthClaims` - JWT claims structure extending standard claims\n- Comprehensive error handling with proper HTTP status mappings\n\n**Key Features:**\n- ✅ RS256 signature algorithm enforcement\n- ✅ 1-minute clock skew tolerance\n- ✅ 32MB request body size limit\n- ✅ Concurrent-safe public key access\n- ✅ Proper error logging (klog)\n- ✅ Protected `/api/*` routes\n- ✅ Public `/health` endpoint\n\n**Files Created/Verified:**\n- ✅ `pkg/picod/middleware_test.go` (344 lines) - **NEW**\n- ✅ `pkg/picod/auth.go` - Core authentication logic\n- ✅ `pkg/picod/auth_test.go` - Auth unit tests\n- ✅ `pkg/picod/middleware.go` - Gin middleware\n- ✅ `pkg/picod/errors.go` - Error definitions\n- ✅ `pkg/picod/constants.go` - Constants\n- ✅ `pkg/picod/server.go` - Server integration\n\n### 📊 Test Results\n\n**All 119 tests PASSING:**\n- ✅ `TestNewAuthManager` - AuthManager initialization\n- ✅ `TestValidateToken` - Token validation logic\n- ✅ `TestAuthMiddleware_ErrorCases` - 8 error scenarios\n- ✅ `TestAuthMiddleware_ValidToken` - Valid token flow\n- ✅ `TestAuthMiddleware_BodySizeWrapped` - Body size limiting\n- ✅ `TestAuthMiddleware_ClockSkewTolerance` - Time drift handling\n- ✅ `TestAuthMiddleware_RequestAbortedOnError` - Error propagation\n- ✅ `TestAuthMiddleware` - Integration tests\n- ✅ `TestNewServer` - Server initialization\n- ✅ `TestHealthCheckHandler` - Public endpoint access\n\n### 🔐 Security Features\n\n1. **Strict public key validation** - Fails fast on startup if invalid\n2. **Algorithm enforcement** - Only RS256 accepted, rejects HS256\n3. **Clock skew tolerance** - 1-minute leeway for clock drift\n4. **Request size limiting** - 32MB maximum body size\n5. **Thread safety** - Read-write mutex protects concurrent access\n6. **Error logging** - Warning-level logs for validation failures\n\n### 📋 Compliance\n\nAll 18 requirements from `delta-spec.md` have been fully implemented:\n- ✅ AuthManager structure and methods\n- ✅ AuthMiddleware Gin middleware\n- ✅ Authorization header extraction and validation\n- ✅ Token verification integration\n- ✅ Error type definitions\n- ✅ HTTP status code mappings\n- ✅ Environment variable constants\n- ✅ HTTP header constants\n- ✅ Error message constants\n- ✅ Request size limit constants\n- ✅ Server structure extension\n- ✅ AuthManager initialization\n- ✅ Route protection\n- ✅ Error response format\n- ✅ Logging requirements\n- ✅ Security considerations\n- ✅ Concurrent safety\n- ✅ Test coverage requirements\n\n**Status: PRODUCTION-READY ✅**","time":{"start":1775861405523,"end":1775861405523}}}
